# üõ†Ô∏è AgencyStack DevOps Rules (Local Windsurf `rules.md`)

## ‚öôÔ∏è Build System & Infrastructure Stack
1. üß± My infrastructure framework is **AgencyStack** ‚Äì a multi-tenant, hardenable, sovereign DevOps toolkit.
2. üì¶ Each component must install via a **bash script under `/scripts/components`** and be controlled via **Makefile targets**.
3. ‚ôªÔ∏è The **installation experience must be idempotent**, local-first, and support automation on airgapped servers.

## üß™ Testing & Validation
4. ‚úÖ Validate all components using `make <component>-status` and `make alpha-check`.
5. üß™ Mock mode must be available for all LLM-powered components (under `/scripts/mock/`) for UI and logic testing.

## üìÅ Filesystem Structure & Conventions
6. üìÇ Do not create files outside of these directories:
   - `/scripts/components/`
   - `/scripts/mock/`
   - `/docs/pages/components/`
   - `/opt/agency_stack/...` for install paths
   - `/var/log/agency_stack/...` for logs
7. üö´ Do not hardcode paths or use `/usr`, `/etc`, or `$HOME`.

## üîí Security & Sovereignty
8. üõ°Ô∏è All installations must:
   - ü™µ Log to `/var/log/agency_stack/components/<component>.log`
   - üß≠ Use client-aware paths like `/opt/agency_stack/clients/${CLIENT_ID}/`
   - üì¥ Avoid cloud APIs unless explicitly enabled with flags (e.g., `--enable-openai`).
9. üóùÔ∏è No centralized authentication unless integrating with self-hosted Keycloak realms.

## üåê Networking & Monitoring
10. üì° If the component uses a port, define it in `component_registry.json` and document in `/docs/pages/ports.md`.
11. üìà Add `/metrics` endpoints when Prometheus-compatible.
12. üìä Set Docker resource limits where applicable.

## üìñ Documentation
13. üìö Each component must have a Markdown doc in `/docs/pages/components/`.
14. üßæ Do not auto-generate docs unless explicitly triggered.
15. ‚úçÔ∏è Use simple English and follow alpha milestone formatting patterns.


CLAUDE INSTALL INSTRUCTION TEMPLATE

You are building a new component installer for AgencyStack, a sovereign infrastructure stack. Follow these DevOps standards strictly:

Installer Script

Create install_<component>.sh under /scripts/components/

Must be hardened, idempotent, and multi-tenant aware

Use /opt/agency_stack/clients/${CLIENT_ID}/ for all client-specific config

Log actions to /var/log/agency_stack/components/<component>.log

Makefile Targets Add the following Make targets:

make <component> ‚Äì install

make <component>-status ‚Äì systemctl or container status check

make <component>-logs ‚Äì tail logs

make <component>-restart ‚Äì restart the service or container

Optional: make <component>-test ‚Äì test interface or API

Component Registry

Add the component to component_registry.json

Set flags: "installed", "makefile", "docs", "hardened", "monitoring", "multi_tenant", "sso" (if applicable)

Documentation

Create /docs/pages/components/<component>.md

Include: overview, install steps, ports, config, security, logs, restart, monitoring

Update /docs/pages/components.md index

Add to /docs/pages/ports.md if ports are exposed

Integration

Make sure it is tracked by make alpha-check

Confirm it emits logs, has status check, and responds to CLI/UI triggers

Security & Monitoring

Ensure TLS if networked

Add /metrics if Prometheus-compatible

Enable container resource limits if Docker-based

Bonus: Mock Mode

If component has APIs, implement mock_<component>.sh or route under /scripts/mock/

This installer must feel polished, auditable, reproducible, and sovereign. Make no assumptions about internet access or centralized secrets.



